<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="The_Apadana_Palace">The Apadana Palace</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Persepolis&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11" title="Edit section: The Apadana Palace"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Main article: <a href="/wiki/Apadana" title="Apadana">Apadana</a></div>
<figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Persepolis_-_statue_of_a_mastiff.jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4d/Persepolis_-_statue_of_a_mastiff.jpg/220px-Persepolis_-_statue_of_a_mastiff.jpg" decoding="async" width="220" height="183" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4d/Persepolis_-_statue_of_a_mastiff.jpg/330px-Persepolis_-_statue_of_a_mastiff.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4d/Persepolis_-_statue_of_a_mastiff.jpg/440px-Persepolis_-_statue_of_a_mastiff.jpg 2x" data-file-width="922" data-file-height="768" /></a><figcaption>Statue of a <a href="/wiki/Mastiff" title="Mastiff">Persian Mastiff</a> found at the <a href="/wiki/Apadana" title="Apadana">Apadana</a>, kept at the <a href="/wiki/National_Museum_of_Iran" title="National Museum of Iran">National Museum of Iran</a>.</figcaption></figure>
<p><a href="/wiki/Darius_I" class="mw-redirect" title="Darius I">Darius I</a> built the greatest palace at Persepolis on the western side of platform. This palace was called the <i><a href="/wiki/Apadana" title="Apadana">Apadana</a></i>.<sup id="cite_ref-44" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-44">&#91;43&#93;</a></sup> The King of Kings used it for official audiences.
</p><p>Foundation tablets of gold and silver were found in two deposition boxes in the foundations of the Palace.<sup id="cite_ref-45" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-45">&#91;44&#93;</a></sup> They contained an inscription by Darius in <a href="/wiki/Old_Persian_cuneiform" title="Old Persian cuneiform">Old Persian cuneiform</a>, which describes the extent of his Empire in broad geographical terms, and is known as the DPh inscription:<sup id="cite_ref-ACH29_46-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-ACH29-46">&#91;45&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-47" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-47">&#91;46&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
<div class="thumb tmulti tright"><div class="thumbinner multiimageinner" style="width:343px;max-width:343px"><div class="trow"><div class="tsingle" style="width:200px;max-width:200px"><div class="thumbimage" style="height:137px;overflow:hidden"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Corner_of_the_Apadana_Darius_the_Great_inscription.jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Corner_of_the_Apadana_Darius_the_Great_inscription.jpg/198px-Corner_of_the_Apadana_Darius_the_Great_inscription.jpg" decoding="async" width="198" height="137" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Corner_of_the_Apadana_Darius_the_Great_inscription.jpg/297px-Corner_of_the_Apadana_Darius_the_Great_inscription.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Corner_of_the_Apadana_Darius_the_Great_inscription.jpg/396px-Corner_of_the_Apadana_Darius_the_Great_inscription.jpg 2x" data-file-width="600" data-file-height="416" /></a></span></div><div class="thumbcaption text-align-center">Gold foundation tablets of Darius I for the <a href="/wiki/Apadana_Palace" class="mw-redirect" title="Apadana Palace">Apadana Palace</a>, in their original stone box. The <a href="/wiki/Apadana_hoard" title="Apadana hoard">Apadana coin hoard</a> had been deposited underneath. <abbr title="circa">c.</abbr><span style="white-space:nowrap;">&#8201;510 BC</span>. Both are kept at the <a href="/wiki/National_Museum_of_Iran" title="National Museum of Iran">National Museum of Iran</a>.</div></div><div class="tsingle" style="width:139px;max-width:139px"><div class="thumbimage" style="height:137px;overflow:hidden"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Deposition_plate_of_Darius_I_in_Persepolis.jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1b/Deposition_plate_of_Darius_I_in_Persepolis.jpg/137px-Deposition_plate_of_Darius_I_in_Persepolis.jpg" decoding="async" width="137" height="137" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1b/Deposition_plate_of_Darius_I_in_Persepolis.jpg/206px-Deposition_plate_of_Darius_I_in_Persepolis.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1b/Deposition_plate_of_Darius_I_in_Persepolis.jpg/274px-Deposition_plate_of_Darius_I_in_Persepolis.jpg 2x" data-file-width="960" data-file-height="958" /></a></span></div><div class="thumbcaption text-align-center">One of the two gold deposition plates. Two more were in silver. They all had the same trilingual inscription (DPh inscription).<sup id="cite_ref-48" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-48">&#91;47&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div></div></div>
<blockquote class="templatequote"><p>Darius the great king, king of kings, king of countries, son of Hystaspes, an Achaemenid. King Darius says: This is the kingdom which I hold, from the <a href="/wiki/Scythians" title="Scythians">Sacae</a> who are beyond <a href="/wiki/Sogdia" title="Sogdia">Sogdia</a>, to <a href="/wiki/Kingdom_of_Kush" title="Kingdom of Kush">Kush</a>, and from <a href="/wiki/Sind" class="mw-redirect" title="Sind">Sind</a> (<a href="/wiki/Old_Persian_language" class="mw-redirect" title="Old Persian language">Old Persian</a>: <span lang="peo"><a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/%F0%90%8F%83%F0%90%8E%A1%F0%90%8E%AF%F0%90%8E%A2%F0%90%8F%81" class="extiw" title="wikt:𐏃𐎡𐎯𐎢𐏁">𐏃𐎡𐎭𐎢𐎺</a></span>, <small>romanized:&#160;</small><span title="Old Persian-language romanization"><i lang="peo-Latn">Hidauv</i></span>, <a href="/wiki/Locative" class="mw-redirect" title="Locative">locative</a> of <span title="Old Persian (ca. 600-400 B.C.)-language romanization"><i lang="peo-Latn"><a href="/wiki/Hindush" title="Hindush">Hiduš</a></i></span>, i.e. "<a href="/wiki/Indus_valley" class="mw-redirect" title="Indus valley">Indus valley</a>") to <a href="/wiki/Lydia" title="Lydia">Lydia</a> (<a href="/wiki/Old_Persian_language" class="mw-redirect" title="Old Persian language">Old Persian</a>: <span lang="peo">Spardâ</span>) – [this is] what Ahuramazda, the greatest of gods, bestowed upon me. May Ahuramazda protect me and my royal house!</p><div class="templatequotecite">—&#8202;<cite>DPh inscription of Darius I in the foundations of the Apadana Palace<sup id="cite_ref-49" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-49">&#91;48&#93;</a></sup></cite></div></blockquote>
<p>The reliefs on the staircases allow one to observe the people from across the empire in their traditional dress, and even the king himself, "down to the smallest detail".<sup id="cite_ref-The_Persians_13-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-The_Persians-13">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
